cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with generating visible-like face images from thermal images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which makes it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel solution that does not require large databases or computationally-intense training, which is relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses contextual loss, which is a technique in image processing and computer vision, making it relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with generating high-quality images, which is relevant to cs.GR (Graphics).
